Based on the epidemic model with nonlinear incidence rate, we study the corresponding pattern dynamics. Through the analysis and the numerical simulation, we obtain two main results. First, we use linear analysis and standard multiple-scale analysis, and gain the exact expressions of amplitude equation. Second, we reveal that an epidemic model with spatial diffusion has rich dynamics by means of numerical simulation in parameters space. The results confirm that spatial motion of individuals can form high density of infectious diseases.

